The notion of time and space

6
00:00:45,870 --> 00:00:48,120
is like a series of snapshots

7
00:00:48,120 --> 00:00:52,180
that record the changes in space as time progresses.

8
00:00:52,180 --> 00:00:54,070
Therefore, speed

9
00:00:54,070 --> 00:00:56,920
is defined by the distance over time,

10
00:00:56,920 --> 00:01:00,500
and in order for the speed of light to be consistent,

11
00:01:00,500 --> 00:01:02,620
the time has to slow down.

12
00:01:02,620 --> 00:01:05,140
In 1908, Minkowski said

13
00:01:05,140 --> 00:01:08,200
in the lecture that is still famous today...

14
00:01:08,950 --> 00:01:16,000

15
